<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Quincy</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Newport, R. I.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>My Government cable me to ascertain and report exactly what your
                            Government and that of Germany have agreed upon with reference to Samoa,
                            in order that precise instructions may be sent to British naval officers
                            and consul. I should be very grateful for immediate answer to that and
                            previous inquiry.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>